{"title_page": "1995\u201396 Meistriliiga", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition        = [[Meistriliiga]]\n  | season             = 1995\u201396\n  | winners            = [[FC Lantana Tallinn|Lantana]]<br>(1st title)\n  | relegated          = [[P\u00e4rnu JK|PJK Kalev]] \n  | continentalcup1    = [[UEFA Cup 1996\u201397|UEFA Cup]]\n  | continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FC Lantana Tallinn|Lantana]]<br>[[FC Flora Tallinn|Flora]]\n  | continentalcup2    = [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n  | continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[JK Tallinna Sadam|Tallinna Sadam]]\n  | continentalcup3    = [[UEFA Intertoto Cup|Intertoto Cup]]\n  | continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[JK Narva Trans|Trans]]\n  | league topscorer   = [[Lembit Rajala]] (16)\n  | total goals        = \n  | average goals      = \n  | biggest home win   = \n  | biggest away win   = \n  | highest attendance = \n  | lowest attendance  = \n  | average attendance = \n  | prevseason         = [[1994\u201395 Meistriliiga|1994\u201395]] \n  | nextseason         = [[1996\u201397 Meistriliiga|1996\u201397]]\n}}\nThe '''1995\u201396 Meistriliiga''' was the fifth season of the [[Meistriliiga]], Estonia's premier football league. [[FC Lantana Tallinn|Lantana]] won their first title.\n\n==Preliminary round==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=LAN|name_LAN=[[FC Lantana Tallinn|Lantana]]\n|team2=NAR|name_NAR=[[JK Narva Trans|Trans]]\n|team3=FLO|name_FLO=[[FC Flora Tallinn|Flora]]\n|team4=SAD|name_SAD=[[JK Tallinna Sadam|Tallinna Sadam]]\n|team5=MAR|name_MAR=[[FC TVMK Tallinn|Tevalte-Marlekor]]\n|team6=TER|name_TER=[[JK Tervis P\u00e4rnu|Tervis]]\n|team7=JEP|name_JEP=[[JK Eesti P\u00f5levkivi J\u00f5hvi|Eesti P\u00f5levkivi J\u00f5hvi]]\n|team8=PJK|name_PJK=[[P\u00e4rnu JK|PJK Kalev]]\n|win_LAN=10|draw_LAN=3|loss_LAN=1|gf_LAN=37|ga_LAN=8\n|win_NAR=6|draw_NAR=4|loss_NAR=4|gf_NAR=22|ga_NAR=16\n|win_FLO=6|draw_FLO=4|loss_FLO=4|gf_FLO=37|ga_FLO=19\n|win_SAD=6|draw_SAD=3|loss