\n==Meistriliiga Transition Tournament==\nEesti P\u00f5levkivi J\u00f5hvi and PJK Kalev, the teams finishing in the last two positions in the preliminary round, faced four best teams of the [[1995-96 Esiliiga]] in the play-off for two places in the [[1996-97 Meistriliiga]].\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=PR\n\n|team1=JEP|name_JEP=[[JK Eesti P\u00f5levkivi J\u00f5hvi|Eesti P\u00f5levkivi J\u00f5hvi]]\n|team2=VAL|name_VAL=[[JK Vall Tallinn|Vall]]\n|team3=NOR|name_NOR=[[FC Norma Tallinn|Norma]]\n|team4=PJK|name_PJK=[[P\u00e4rnu JK|PJK Kalev]]\n|team5=D\u00dcN|name_D\u00dcN=[[FC D\u00fcnamo Tallinn|D\u00fcnamo]]\n|team6=TJK|name_TJK=[[Tallinna Jalgpalliklubi|TJK]]\n|win_JEP=7|draw_JEP=0|loss_JEP=3|gf_JEP=23|ga_JEP=7\n|win_VAL=7|draw_VAL=0|loss_VAL=3|gf_VAL=18|ga_VAL=9|status_VAL=P\n|win_NOR=5|draw_NOR=2|loss_NOR=3|gf_NOR=13|ga_NOR=11\n|win_PJK=4|draw_PJK=2|loss_PJK=4|gf_PJK=12|ga_PJK=20|status_PJK=R\n|win_D\u00dcN=2|draw_D\u00dcN=2|loss_D\u00dcN=6|gf_D\u00dcN=8|ga_D\u00dcN=14\n|win_TJK=1|draw_TJK=2|loss_TJK=7|gf_TJK=9|ga_TJK=22\n|col_P=green1|text_P=[[1996\u201397 Meistriliiga]]\n|result1=P|result2=P\n|col_R=red1|text_R=[[1996\u201397 Esiliiga]]\n|result3=R|result4=R|result5=R|result6=R\n\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Top scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank\n!Player\n!Club\n!Goals<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/esttops.html|title=Estonia - List of Topscorers|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Lembit Rajala]]||Flora||align=center|16\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Maksim Gruznov]]||Lantana||align=center|12\n|-\n|rowspan=5 align=center|3\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Andrei Borissov]]||Lantana||rowspan=5 align=center|8\n|-\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Boriss Nejolov]]||Narva Trans\n|-\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Ivan O'Konnel-Bronin]]||Tervis P\u00e4rnu/Flora\n|-\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Aleksandr Olerski]]||Tevalte/Marlekor\n|-\n|{{flagicon|EST}} [[Dmitri Ustritski]]||